-- NewPage Bonds Fall Most in Four Months After CEO, Chairman Resign Posts
-- John Detrixhe
-- 2010-06-15T14:33:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/newpage-bonds-fall-most-in-four-months-after-ceo-chairman-resign-posts.html

          
          
             NewPage Corp. bonds fell the most in
four months after  E. Thomas Curley  resigned as president, chief
executive officer and a director of the maker coated paper.  
 The company’s 11.375 percent notes due in 2014 declined 2.7
cents to 90.7 cents on the dollar to yield 14.2 percent as of
10:21 a.m., according to Trace, the bond-price reporting system
of the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority. It was biggest
drop for the senior secured debt Feb. 8.  
 NewPage appointed  Robert Nardelli , CEO of Cerberus
Operating & Advisory Co. and a former chairman of Chrysler LLC
and Home Depot Inc., as a director and non-executive chairman,
the Miamisburg, Ohio-based company said today in a statement
distributed by PR Newswire.  
 Mark Suwyn , chairman and director, and  Michael Edicola  vice
president of human resources, also resigned from their positions
at NewPage, according to the statement.  
 The company, North America’s largest maker of coated paper
based on production capacity, is a unit of NewPage Group Inc.,
which is owned by Cerberus Capital Management LP.  
